    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Wight-Commander — Level 4 Standard</strong></p><p><em>Undead, Medium</em></p><p>Stamina 32 | Speed 5 | Size M | Stability 1</p><p>A draugr with intelligence — rare and dangerous. This wight retains the tactical mind it had in life, coordinating the undead siege with precision that ordinary draugr cannot achieve. It commands a twelve-draugr battering ram crew at the main gate, directing synchronized impacts with chilling efficiency.</p><hr><h3>Attacks</h3><p><strong>Command Strike</strong> (Melee, Might): +3 vs Might; 8 damage. <em>Effect:</em> All undead within Close Burst 3 make a free strike against the nearest target as a triggered action.</p><p><strong>Coordinating Howl</strong> (Close Burst 5, Presence): All undead in range gain +2 to attack rolls until end of the Wight-Commander's next turn.</p><hr><h3>Features</h3><p><strong>Tactical Intelligence:</strong> The Wight-Commander cannot be fooled by simple feints. Misdirection requires a Hard Intuition test (TN 15) to execute against it.</p><p><strong>Ram Coordination:</strong> As long as the Wight-Commander is active, the battering ram operates at full efficiency. If the Commander is disrupted (dazed, killed, or driven back), the ram loses coordination and takes 2 rounds to reorganize.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>TACTICAL GUIDANCE:</strong></p><ul><li>The Wight-Commander does not fight the party directly unless forced. It commands from behind the ram crew, issuing Coordinating Howl to boost their effectiveness.</li><li>If the party targets the Commander specifically, it fights with Command Strike — forcing nearby undead to also attack, making it costly to engage in melee.</li><li>The Commander is the <em>nerve center</em> of the main gate assault. Killing or driving it off is the most efficient way to break the battering ram's momentum.</li><li>If dazed or stunned, the ram immediately loses its synchronized pattern. The 2-round reorganization window is the party's best opportunity to shore up the main gate.</li></ul><p><strong>MONTAGE INTEGRATION:</strong> The Wight-Commander appears in Crisis C (Main Gate) of the Three-Crisis Montage. It is not a separate combat encounter unless the montage generates a contingent fight at the main gate.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
